				</TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6427">Mitch King</A></FONT> <font class="afont">( was very helpful )</font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2">&nbsp;</TD></tr><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="10%"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"></TD><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="90%"><font class="bfont"> I dunno about this deck, it looks as if it could be cool though.  I&#39;m not sure about the use of Pippin, very nice in some aspects of course.  It doesn&#39;t strike me as a deck based particularly strongly around a choke strategy, still every twilight can count.  If I had money for every time someone&#39;s said "just one more twilight" during a match ;o)<br>
<br>
I&#39;m also not sure that people might not look at this and think you&#39;re advocating the use of Westfarthing and Pippin game text at the same time should you pull Aragorn and/or Gandalf in your starting hand ::grins:: I know this is obviously against the timing rules but you do need to be specific on stuff like that, you never know who&#39;s reading ::points to herself:: I was bad at timing actions when I was a newbie for instance.  Maybe some extra detail in your strategy section would be of some use.<br>
<br>
Fellowship looks quite strong but the shadow side looks a little top heavy as far as minion twilight costs go.  Could prove a little problematic against choke type decks, particularly early in the game.  Also looks like it may have some problems against ranger/archery FP, even with a couple of uruk scouts in to take care possible ARV a lot of good ranger decks will have strong enough fellowships to hurt you...and you have to win before you can wound/burden with many of your conditions and minion text.  Anyway, just my tuppence worth. <font size=1>(0 tp, Double-Edged Sword)</font> </FONT></TD>
